Topic.PrintSuperHeading: Assessment Requirements for ICTPRG507 Implement security for applications

Text.p: Evidence of the following must be provided:
Note: If a specific volume or frequency is not stated, then evidence must be provided at least once.
recognise the mathematics required for programming algorithms.

Gather evidence to demonstrate consistent performance in conditions that are safe and replicate the workplace. Noise levels, production flow, interruptions and time variances must be typical of those experienced in the programming and software development industry, and include access to:
the appropriate learning and assessment support, when required.
Assessors must satisfy NVR/AQTF assessor requirements.
Companion volumes available from the IBSA website: http://www.ibsa.org.au/companion_volumes - http://companion_volumes.vetnet.education.gov.au/Pages/TrainingPackage.aspx?pid=18
